<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-03-06T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-03-06T12:00:00-05:00" n="938" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d938">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/8837:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Yugoslavia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Lane</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Belgrade</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-03-06T18:00:00+01:00">March 6,
                                    1941—6 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 7:12 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>155. For the Under Secretary. I learn from a reliable source that Fotić
                            who is one of the most highly regarded Yugoslav diplomatic
                            representatives has been telegraphing fully his conversations with you
                            and that these reports have had an excellent effect in fortifying
                            attitude of high officials here. It has been suggested to me that the
                            more ammunition you can give him the more efficacious the results will
                            be here.</p>
                        <p>As I know that you are on close terms with Fotić I am not forwarding the
                            foregoing as a suggestion, but merely for your information.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Lane</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>